---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Fireplace Safety — Children, Pets, Clearances | Heat & Glo"
  description="Heat & Glo fireplace safety: protective screens, clearance-to-combustibles, child and pet safety, and proper operation guidelines for every Heat & Glo product."
  noIndex={true}
>
  <main class="max-w-page mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="uppercase tracking-wide text-sm text-orange-700 font-semibold">Fireplace Safety</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-2">Built to be enjoyed safely.</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-neutral-700 max-w-2xl">
        Every Heat & Glo fireplace is engineered, tested, and listed to applicable safety standards.
        That said, real safety in your home depends on a few practices that no amount of engineering
        can replace. Read these before your first fire of the season.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Protective screens</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
          Glass-front gas fireplaces remain hot to the touch for some time after the flame is shut off.
          Heat & Glo's protective screens, available as a standard accessory, prevent direct contact
          with hot glass for households with children, pets, or older family members. Strongly
          recommended for any home where vulnerable family members share space with the fireplace.
        </p>
        <a href="/fireplace-safety/safety-screen-request/" class="inline-block mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-orange-700 underline">
          Request a safety screen →
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="border rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Clearance-to-combustibles</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700">
          Every Heat & Glo unit has specific clearance requirements that must be observed when
          installing mantels, surrounds, and adjacent finish materials. Clearances are listed in
          the installation manual for each model. Confirm clearances with your installer before
          finalizing any mantel design.
        </p>
        <a href="/manuals/" class="inline-block mt-4 text-sm font-medium text-orange-700 underline">
          Find your installation manual →
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold mb-2 text-amber-900">Annual professional service</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-900">
        Heat & Glo recommends annual inspection and service of every gas fireplace by a qualified
        service technician. Your authorized dealer can schedule annual service and confirm any
        wear-component replacements needed for safe operation. Don't skip it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t pt-10">
      <p class="text-neutral-600">
        Need annual service or have a safety concern? <a href="/where-to-buy/" class="underline">Find your authorized dealer</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
